Description: Sherd of shoulder with turn to neck of large North Ionian black-figured pottery vessel, dinos or krater; flat and thick shoulder; interior reserved; exterior slipped white; upper part of shoulder glazed with incised lotus and bud frieze with much added white and red; band below, and animal frieze, part of lion to left with rosettes as fill.
Curator's comments: From same vase as 1926,1117.3 and probably Boston, MFA 86.543.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.926)
